
[1]rhomb

   RHOMB, n. [L. rhombus; Gr from to turn or whirl round, to wander, to
   roam or rove; literally, a deviating square.]

   In geometry, an oblique angled parallelogram, or a quadrilateral figure
   whose sides are equal and parallel, but the angles unequal, two of the
   angles being obtuse and two acute. It consists of two equal and right
   cones united at the base.
